BREAD PUDDING
4 eggs				1/4 tsp salt
2 c milk			2 1/2 c dry bread cubes
1/3 c sugar			 (about 3 1/2 slices)
1/2 tsp cinnamon		1/2 c raisins (optional)
1/2 tsp vanilla

Beat together eggs, milk, sugar, cinnamon, vanilla, and salt.  Place
bread cubes in an 8x1 1/2-inch round baking dish.  Sprinkle raisins
over bread.  Pour egg mixture over all.  Bake at 325 for 40 to 45
minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.  Cool
slightly before serving.


